 -5)$.\n\n(a) Find the equation of the line of symmetry of the curve.\n\n(b) Write the equation of the curve in the form \\quad $y = (x + a)^2 + b$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"y ="}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper23-Q15","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper23","qnum":15,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/23/O/N/25 Q15","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Factorise.\n\n(a) $x^2 - 7x + 12$\n\n(b) $5x + 10y + 6ny + 3nx$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper23-Q16","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper23","qnum":16,"marks":5,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.7","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sequences","qtype":"sequences","g":"sequence","src":"0580/23/O/N/25 Q16","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The table shows three sequences.\n\nComplete the table to show the $n$th term of each sequence.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper23-Q17","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper23","qnum":17,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"2.11","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sketching curves","qtype":"sketching curves","g":"graph","src":"0580/23/O/N/25 Q17","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) Sketch the graph of \\quad $y = \\cos x$ \\quad for $0^\\circ \\leqslant x \\leqslant 360^\\circ$.\n\n(b) $\\cos x^\\circ = \\dfrac{1}{\\sqrt{2}}$ \\quad and $x$ is a **reflex** angle.\n\nFind the value of $x$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"x ="}}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"sketch"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper23-Q18","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper23","qnum":18,"marks":2,"topics":["